== Pacific Islands Participating == There are 14 Pacific islands participating in the sea level and climate monitoring project. These islands include * Cook Islands * Federated States of Micronesia * Fiji * Kiribati * Marshall Islands * Nauru * Niue * Palau * Papua New Guinea * Samoa * Solomon Islands * Tonga * Tuvalu * Vanuatu {{Orphan|date=March 2011}}
{{Expand Japanese|南太平洋潮位・気候監視プロジェクト|date=January 2010}} '''South Pacific Sea Level and Climate Monitoring Project''' (SPSLCMP) is a project initiated by [[government of Australia]].
